Crypt-Smithy

Crypt::Smithy implements an algorithm used to embed a code in the
2006 judgement in the Da Vinci Code copyright case.
Crypthographically it is highly insecure and is for entertainment
and educational purposes only.
    

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Crypt::Smithy

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Crypt-Smithy

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Crypt-Smithy

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Crypt-Smithy

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Crypt-Smithy/


